Every United game in isolation for a while for me, no, this is moving in right direction after win, we've that many games coming up, December full of pitfalls and opportunities - no point looking beyond next game , try to restore pride after disgraceful month. Sunday a huge test.

Sancho wants to take players on. He gets the ball and looks for options ahead of him. Now needs a run of games to grow in confidence but we've seen this week, at last, what he's got, and he's much better on the right than left.

Big, gritty, determined win. Needed that win, didn't want Europa. Turgid for long periods, but ended well. Sancho was decent Saturday - really positive today. Donny showed he offers us positives, and tho Fred has faults, we all know, covered so much ground today and drove team.
